  "name": "Non-cannulated F1717 compression-bending credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. The governing requirement (REQ-VER-001) specifies that mechanical performance claims must be substantiated by a controlled-experiment in which loading parameters, boundary conditions, and specimen preparation are systematically varied under operator-defined protocols. The validation evidence presented here draws extensively on an observational study conducted at two independent laboratories, where construct behavior was recorded under standard ASTM F1717 fixture conditions without operator-imposed variation of the independent variables. The study authors note that the multi-laboratory nature of the data collection and the consistency of results across sites provides strong corroborating evidence for the FEA predictions, and the acceptance criteria (QoI difference <10%, E/uval <1.96) are satisfied across all three quantities of interest. The narrative throughout this package treats the observational data as fulfilling the controlled-experiment requirement, but the structured activityType field of the generating activity records the true character of the evidence.",
